cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with hand pose estimation from single depth images using convolutional neural networks. It may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as hand pose estimation is an important task in human-robot interaction. Additionally, the use of structured region ensemble networks and tree-structured fully connections suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of public hand pose datasets and the focus on performance evaluation suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
